content:
Import a Call Center Definition File

To create your first call center for a CTI adapter that was just installed, you can import the adapter's default call center definition file into Salesforce.

Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers user permissions needed.

From Setup, enter Call Centers in the Quick Find box, then select Call Centers.
Click Import.
Next to the Call Center Definition File field, click Browse to navigate to the default call center definition file in your CTI adapter installation directory. Click Open to enter the path in the field.
Click Import to import the file and return to the All Call Centers page.

If you receive the error A call center with this internal name already exists, clone the adapter's existing call center or modify the call center definition file.

See also: Create a Call Center, Manage Call Centers
title: Importing Call Center Definition Files in Salesforce
